---
/**
 * Home — "Swiss / editorial, mono-led" direction, three-track desktop layout.
 *
 * The desktop width is used by ADDING COLUMNS, not by widening the prose: the
 * reading column stays at a ~66-character measure (~40rem), and the recovered
 * horizontal space holds two margin rails —
 *   left:  a section index (sticky nav), and
 *   right: a persistent LIVE telemetry aside (the "this page monitors itself"
 *          thesis, given a permanent home: req/s + sparkline, targets, alerts,
 *          build, and the latest homelab commit).
 * On narrow screens it collapses to one column (live panel as a band, index
 * hidden). See ~/Projects/portfolio-design-research.md, Part 5.
 *
 * Type rule: SERIF for human content (name, project titles, prose); MONO for
 * everything systemic (labels, numbers, nav, live data). Zero radius, hairline
 * rules, no shadows, one reserved accent. Live wiring is the external module
 * public/home.js so the CSP stays inline-free.
 */
import { social } from '../data/site';
---

<div class="home">
  <header class="masthead">
    <div class="masthead__id">
      <p class="eyebrow">Infrastructure · Systems · Linux</p>
      <h1 class="name">Henry Dowd</h1>
      <p class="tagline">I build and run infrastructure from the bare metal up.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="masthead__side">
      <nav class="linknav" aria-label="Portfolio pages">
        <a href="/cv/">CV</a>
        <span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
        <a href="/about/">About</a>
        <span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
        <a href="/homelab/">Homelab</a>
        <span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
        <a href="/status/">Status</a>
      </nav>
      <nav class="social" aria-label="Contact">
        {social.map(({ key, href, value, external }) => (
          <a class="social__item" href={href} {...(external ? { target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener' } : {})}>
            <span class="social__k">{key}</span>
            <span class="social__v">{value}</span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <div class="grid">
    <nav class="rail" aria-label="Sections">
      <ol class="index">
        <li><a href="#intro">About</a></li>
        <li><a href="#work">Projects</a></li>
        <li><a href="#approach">Skills</a></li>
        <li><a href="#infra">Infrastructure</a></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="rail__note">Self-hosted on k3s. This page runs on the same platform it reports on.</p>
    </nav>

    <div class="body">
      <section id="intro" class="block">
        <h2 class="block__h">About</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          I build software and then run it myself, on hardware I own. Most of it
          lands on a small Kubernetes cluster at home, the same cluster that
          serves this page and feeds the panel on the right. I'm drawn to the
          unglamorous parts: deploys that don't wake you up, and monitoring that
          notices a problem before a user does.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="work" class="block">
        <h2 class="block__h">Projects</h2>

        <article class="entry entry--featured">
          <p class="entry__kicker">
            <span class="live__dot" data-dot="cluster" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            The platform this page runs on
          </p>
          <div class="entry__head">
            <h3><a href="/homelab/">Homelab platform</a></h3>
            <p class="entry__meta">Proxmox · k3s · ArgoCD · VictoriaMetrics</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            A Kubernetes cluster I run at home on Proxmox. It's all GitOps: I push
            to my own Gitea, ArgoCD brings the cluster in line with the repo, and
            VictoriaMetrics keeps an eye on the rest. It hosts Nextcloud, Immich
            and a handful of other things, including this page, which gets scraped
            by the same stack that's filling the panel on the right.
          </p>
          <p class="entry__links">
            <a href="/homelab/">The build in detail →</a>
            <a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/homelab" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source ↗</a>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="entry">
          <div class="entry__head">
            <h3><a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/paraphrase_detector" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Paraphrase detector</a></h3>
            <p class="entry__meta">Python · scikit-learn · Sentence-BERT · final-year project</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            Works out whether two sentences mean the same thing. Instead of
            fine-tuning a big model and treating it as a black box, I combined four
            features you can actually inspect into a logistic regression: BERT
            similarity, tree-edit distance over the parse, word overlap, and a
            length ratio. On the MSR Paraphrase Corpus it edged out BERT on its own
            (0.79 ROC AUC against 0.78), and each of the four features held up as
            a significant signal in its own right.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="entry">
          <div class="entry__head">
            <h3><a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/nextkeep" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NextKeep</a></h3>
            <p class="entry__meta">Android · AI-built · Nextcloud Notes</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            A notes app for Android, built end to end with an AI coding agent while
            I shaped the design and reviewed its output: the feel of Google Keep,
            without Google keeping the notes. It syncs with my self-hosted Nextcloud
            and keeps everything on the device first, so it still works offline, with
            QR-code login, a markdown editor and dynamic theming. Android isn't my
            field; the experiment was how far careful direction could take a model on
            a real, shippable app.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="entry">
          <div class="entry__head">
            <h3><a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/PDF-Sorter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF-Sorter</a></h3>
            <p class="entry__meta">Python · Tesseract OCR</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            A desktop tool that files PDFs by what's inside them rather than what
            they're named. It reads the text, falls back to OCR on scans, and sorts
            against rules you set. I wrote it for the moment you're staring down a
            few hundred invoices with no patience left; it ships as one Windows
            installer with Tesseract bundled in.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="approach" class="block">
        <h2 class="block__h">Skills</h2>
        <dl class="skills">
          <div><dt>Linux &amp; bare metal</dt><dd>Arch Linux · Proxmox · ZFS · systemd</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Networking</dt><dd>TCP/IP · WireGuard · split-horizon DNS · reverse proxies</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Containers &amp; GitOps</dt><dd>Kubernetes · ArgoCD · Helm · Sealed Secrets</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Observability</dt><dd>VictoriaMetrics · Grafana · Alertmanager · restic</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Languages</dt><dd>C · Python · Java · Bash · SQL</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </section>

    </div>

    <aside class="aside" aria-label="Live homelab telemetry">
      <div class="aside__inner">
      <div class="readout">
        <p class="readout__head" aria-live="polite">
          <span class="live__dot" data-dot="cluster" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span data-live-state>connecting…</span> · self-monitored
        </p>
        <dl class="metrics">
          <div class="metric metric--lead">
            <dt>req/s · this service</dt>
            <dd>
              <span data-rate>—</span>
              <svg class="spark" data-spark viewBox="0 0 120 26" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
                <polyline class="spark__line" fill="none" points="" />
              </svg>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="metric"><dt>targets up</dt><dd data-targets>—</dd></div>
          <div class="metric"><dt>alerts firing</dt><dd data-alerts>—</dd></div>
          <div class="metric"><dt>running build</dt><dd data-build>—</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div class="latest">
        <p class="readout__head">latest change</p>
        <p class="latest__body" data-latest>—</p>
      </div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>

  <section id="infra" class="infra" aria-labelledby="infra-h">
    <h2 class="block__h" id="infra-h">Infrastructure</h2>
    <p class="infra__intro">
      All of this runs on a single Dell OptiPlex under my desk; Proxmox on the bare
      metal, a two-node k3s cluster sitting on top. Traffic gets in two ways, from the
      public internet through a Cloudflare tunnel with nothing forwarded and no port
      open to the world, and from the house LAN through my own DNS. What follows is
      the whole path it takes, from the request arriving down to the disk it lands on.
    </p>

    <figure class="v-nest-fig" role="group" aria-label="Homelab infrastructure as nested containment: the Proxmox host holds its hardware, the k3s control and worker VMs (which contain the k3s cluster of ingress, apps including this page, and platform services), and the WireGuard, Technitium and AMP LXCs alongside; public traffic enters via a Cloudflare tunnel and LAN traffic via Technitium DNS, and restic backs up off-site to Backblaze B2.">
      <div class="v-nest">
        <div class="vn-sources">
          <div class="vn-src">
            <span class="chip">Internet <i>henrydowd.dev</i></span>
            <span class="vn-down" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
            <span class="vn-edge">Cloudflare tunnel · no open ports</span>
          </div>
          <div class="vn-src">
            <span class="chip">LAN <i>*.lan</i></span>
            <span class="vn-down" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
            <span class="vn-edge">Technitium DNS</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cbox cbox--host">
          <span class="cbox__tag">Proxmox host · under the desk</span>
          <div class="vn-row">
            <span class="row-lab">hardware</span>
            <span class="chip">i5-14500T <i>24 GB</i></span>
            <span class="chip">ZFS RAID-1 <i>2×2 TB</i></span>
          </div>
          <div class="cbox cbox--vms">
            <span class="cbox__tag">k3s VMs · control + worker</span>
            <div class="cbox cbox--k3s">
              <span class="cbox__tag">k3s cluster</span>
              <div class="vn-row">
                <span class="row-lab">edge</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="traefik"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Traefik</span>
                <span class="chip">MetalLB <i>.200</i></span>
                <span class="chip">cert-manager</span>
              </div>
              <div class="vn-row">
                <span class="row-lab">apps</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="gitea"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Gitea</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="nextcloud"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Nextcloud</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="immich"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Immich</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="collabora"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Collabora</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="kiwix"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Kiwix</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="file-parser"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>File-Parser</span>
                <span class="chip chip--here" data-target="portfolio"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Portfolio <i>this page</i></span>
              </div>
              <div class="vn-row">
                <span class="row-lab">platform</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="argocd"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>ArgoCD</span>
                <span class="chip">Sealed Secrets</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="longhorn"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Longhorn</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="victoriametrics"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>VictoriaMetrics</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="grafana"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Grafana</span>
                <span class="chip" data-target="alertmanager"><span class="chip__dot" hidden aria-hidden="true"></span>Alertmanager</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="vn-row">
            <span class="row-lab">lxcs</span>
            <span class="chip chip--ext">WireGuard</span>
            <span class="chip chip--ext">Technitium</span>
            <span class="chip chip--ext">AMP</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="vn-arrows" aria-hidden="true"><span>↓ restic</span></div>
        <div class="vn-out"><span class="chip chip--ext">Backblaze B2 <i>off-site</i></span></div>
      </div>
      <figcaption class="infra__foot">
        The highlighted node is this very page, running as one more pod inside the
        cluster. The boxes nest the way the system actually does: the k3s cluster on
        its control and worker VMs, those on the Proxmox host, the LXCs and the disks
        alongside them. A node carries a <b>live dot</b> only when it's an actual
        scrape target, coloured by that component's current health; the rest are
        structural. The only path that leaves the host is restic, pushing backups
        off-site to Backblaze; the live figures in the panel above are scraped from
        the same VictoriaMetrics sitting a box away, which keeps 30 days of history,
        while the datasets snapshot daily and restic ships an encrypted copy off-site
        every night.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>
</div>

<!-- Live wiring is a same-origin external module so the CSP stays script-src 'self'. -->
<script type="module" src="/home.js"></script>

<style>
  .home {
    --rule: var(--line);
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  /* ---- Masthead ---- */
  .masthead {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.55rem;
  }
  .eyebrow::before { content: ""; width: 1.6rem; height: 2px; background: var(--accent); flex: none; }
  .name {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(3.2rem, 9vw, 5.6rem);
    line-height: 0.94;
    letter-spacing: -0.022em;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .tagline {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.4vw, 1.5rem);
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0.55rem 0 0;
    max-width: 40rem;
  }
  .live__dot { width: 9px; height: 9px; background: var(--ink-soft); flex: none; }
  .live__dot.is-ok { background: var(--ok); animation: home-pulse 2.6s ease-in-out infinite; }
  .live__dot.is-warn { background: var(--warn); }
  .live__dot.is-err { background: var(--err); }
  @keyframes home-pulse { 0%, 100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: 0.35; } }

  .rule { border: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); margin: 1.5rem 0 0; }

  /* ---- Three-track grid (collapses to one column) ---- */
  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    grid-template-areas: "body" "aside";
    gap: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .rail { grid-area: rail; display: none; font-family: var(--mono); align-self: start; }
  .body { grid-area: body; max-width: 40rem; }
  .aside { grid-area: aside; align-self: start; }

  @media (min-width: 66rem) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 11rem minmax(0, 1fr) 16rem;
      grid-template-areas: "rail body aside";
      gap: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem);
    }
    .rail { display: block; position: sticky; top: 1.5rem; }
    /* The aside stretches to the full grid-row height so its left hairline
       reads as a continuous "instrument rail"; the panel itself is pinned. */
    .aside {
      align-self: stretch;
      border-left: 1px solid var(--rule);
      padding-left: clamp(1.25rem, 1.8vw, 1.75rem);
    }
    .aside__inner { position: sticky; top: 1.5rem; }
  }

  /* ---- Left rail: section index ---- */
  .index { list-style: none; margin: 0 0 1.75rem; padding: 0; }
  .index li { padding: 0.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .index li:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .index a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.15s ease; }
  .index a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .index a.is-active { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
  .rail__note { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }

  /* ---- Reading column ---- */
  .block { padding: 2.75rem 0; }
  .block:first-child { padding-top: 0; }
  .block + .block { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .block__h {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .lede { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.9vw, 1.85rem); line-height: 1.45; margin: 0; color: var(--ink); }

  .entry { padding: 1.6rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .entry:first-of-type { border-top: 0; padding-top: 0.25rem; }
  .entry__head { margin-bottom: 0.7rem; }
  .entry h3 { font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin: 0; }
  .entry h3 a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; }
  .entry h3 a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .entry h3 a[target="_blank"]::after { content: " ↗"; color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.7em; }
  /* Tech tokens read as a clean mono stack line; muted so the accent stays a signal. */
  .entry__meta { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0.5rem 0 0; }
  /* Body prose only — scoped to the entry's own direct <p> so it can't reach the
     meta (a <p> inside .entry__head) or the kicker, both of which are mono. */
  .entry > p:not(.entry__kicker) { font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 1.02rem; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; color: var(--ink); }
  /* Link row under the flagship entry: mono, muted, higher specificity than the
     entry-prose rule above so it isn't set as body sans. */
  .entry > p.entry__links {
    display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1.25rem; margin: 0.9rem 0 0;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.8rem;
  }
  .entry__links a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; }
  .entry__links a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .entry__links a[target="_blank"]::after { content: " ↗"; color: var(--ink-soft); }

  /* Flagship: the platform the whole page is about. A live-tinted kicker lifts
     it out of the equal-weight stack and ties it to the telemetry — the dot
     shares the cluster's live state, so it pulses the same colour as the panel. */
  .entry__kicker {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.66rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 0.8rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .skills { margin: 0; }
  .skills div { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 9rem) 1fr; gap: 0.5rem 1.5rem; padding: 0.65rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .skills div:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .skills dt { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.78rem; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0; }
  .skills dd { margin: 0; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.95rem; }

  /* Right column: the page switcher (shared .linknav) sits top-right aligned
     with the eyebrow, with the contact list beneath it. */
  .masthead__side { padding-top: 0.15rem; min-width: 15rem; }

  /* Social links: a vertical, hairline-ruled contact block on the right — label
     and value on one row — balancing the name against the right edge. */
  .social {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--mono);
  }
  .social__item {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 5rem 1fr; gap: 0.9rem; align-items: baseline;
    padding: 0.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); text-decoration: none;
  }
  .social__item:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .social__k { font-size: 0.62rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .social__v { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--ink); }
  .social__item:hover .social__v { color: var(--accent); }

  /* ---- Right aside: live telemetry ---- */
  .readout { border-top: 2px solid var(--accent); padding-top: 0.8rem; }
  .readout__head {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .metrics { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(6rem, 1fr)); gap: 0.75rem 1.5rem; margin: 0; }
  .metric dt { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.66rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0 0 0.2rem; }
  .metric dd { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 1.3rem; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; margin: 0; line-height: 1.05; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.55rem; }
  .metric--lead dd { font-size: 1.75rem; }
  .spark { width: 64px; height: 20px; flex: none; }
  .spark__line { stroke: var(--accent); stroke-width: 1.5; vector-effect: non-scaling-stroke; }

  .latest { margin-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); padding-top: 0.9rem; }
  .latest__body { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.82rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--ink); margin: 0; }

  @media (min-width: 66rem) {
    /* In the narrow aside column, stack the metrics as hairline-ruled rows. */
    .metrics { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0; }
    .metric { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: 0.6rem 0; }
    .metric--lead { border-top: 0; padding-top: 0; }
    .metric dd { justify-content: space-between; }
  }

  /* ---- Infrastructure — nested-containment schematic (full-width, below the grid) ---- */
  .infra { padding-top: 2.75rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .infra__intro {
    font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 1.02rem; line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink); max-width: 44rem; margin: 0 0 2.25rem;
  }
  .v-nest-fig { margin: 0; }

  /* Node chip */
  .chip {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.78rem; line-height: 1.25;
    padding: 0.38rem 0.62rem; border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: var(--surface); color: var(--ink); white-space: nowrap;
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.42rem;
  }
  .chip i { font-style: normal; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .chip--here {
    border-color: var(--accent); border-left-width: 3px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 9%, transparent);
  }
  .chip--ext { border-style: dashed; background: transparent; }
  /* "this page" dot — home.js recolours it to live cluster health. */
  .chip__dot { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--accent); flex: none; }
  .chip__dot[hidden] { display: none; }
  .chip__dot.is-ok { background: var(--ok); animation: home-pulse 2.6s ease-in-out infinite; }
  .chip__dot.is-warn { background: var(--warn); }
